You're missing the `BindingContext`. The page doesn't know which object to bind against. You need to set it — typically in the code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Also ensure** your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or inherits `ObservableObject` from the MVVM Toolkit) so the UI updates when properties change:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title = "Hello";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description = "World";
}
```

Alternatively, you can set `BindingContext` directly in XAML using `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType` for compiled bindings, which also gives you compile-time checking.
